#Approach:

Two Sum – HashMap Approach

Is problem me hume do numbers find karne hain jinka sum target ke equal ho.
Iske liye hum HashMap use karte hain jisme number ko key aur uska index value me store karte hain.

Array traverse karte waqt har element ke liye check karte hain ki target - current element
(pehle se map me present hai ya nahi). Agar present hai, to iska matlab hume required pair mil gaya.

Agar required number map me mil jaye, to uska index aur current index return kar do.
Agar nahi mile, to current number aur uska index map me store kar do future ke liye.

Is tarah hum ek hi traversal me answer find kar lete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target) {
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        for(int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){
            int moreNeeded = target - nums[i];

            if(map.containsKey(moreNeeded)){
                int[] ans = {map.get(moreNeeded), i};
                return ans;
            }
            else{
                map.put(nums[i], i);
            }
        }
        return new int[]{-1, -1};
    }
}
